{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-blog-tsx","path":"/performance/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Several practical ways to improve site performance with React."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For months, we have worked on web performance for our site. It is a tough journey, because even if you know all the good principles (less bundle size, less useless import, lazyload whenever you can), it could be still quite difficult to find good solutions. In this article, I am going to share what I have learnt during these months with some examples."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why site performance is even more important today"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As users, we don't like slow website, and "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://developers.google.com/search/blog/2020/11/timing-for-page-experience"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"so does Google"}]},{"type":"text","value":": from May 2021, Google Search take page experience into account, in another words, site performance is linked to SEO directly."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How to measure performance"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How to improve web performance for Google (and also for our users) ? Like making improvement for SEO, first of all, we need to speak the language of Google. It has its own metrics to evaluate our site performance."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{}